[node name="Laws" type="RichTextLabel" parent="Scroll/VBox"]
layout_mode = 2
size_flags_horizontal = 3
custom_minimum_size = Vector2(0, 400)
theme_override_font_sizes/normal_font_size = 17
bbcode_enabled = true
text = "[b]How to play[/b]
• Enter an [b]angle[/b] in degrees (0° = right, 90° = up on screen) and an [b]acceleration[/b] in m/s², then press Enter.
• Your puck slides with [b]friction[/b] slowing you by 5 m/s² along motion (floor drag).
• [b]Distance[/b] and [b]bearing to the monster[/b] are shown in meters and degrees so you can aim.

[b]Momentum & collisions[/b]
• [b]p = m·v[/b] (momentum). When you hit the monster, the engine applies [b]equal-and-opposite impulses[/b] along the contact normal ([b]Newton's 3rd[/b]).
• With different masses, the split of speeds after a bump matches the same idea as [b]1D elastic collisions[/b]—heavier bodies change velocity less.

[b]Monster surprise[/b]
• Each time you submit a move, the monster also gets a [b]random shove[/b]. The in-game panel shows the [b]next[/b] random [b]angle[/b] and [b]acceleration[/b] that will be applied to the monster [b]when you press Enter[/b], so you can plan one step ahead.

[b]Danger zone[/b]
• The red ring is lethal to [b]you[/b]. Stay on the green safe platform.
"
fit_content = true
autowrap_mode = 3

